article.description: Heather Ezell was 8-for-8 from the free throw line in the last 35 seconds and finished with 19 points as Iowa State (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) upset No. 14 Kansas State (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) 60-50 on Saturday.
article.headline: Ezell hits free throws to clinch Cyclones victory
article.linkText: Ezell clutch in Iowa State's upset of K-State
article.story:
AMES, Iowa -- Heather Ezell was 8-for-8 from the free throw line in the last 35 seconds and finished with 19 points as Iowa State (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) upset No. 14 Kansas State (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) 60-50 on Saturday in the Big 12 Conference.

Ezell was just 3-for-7 from the field, but she hit a big 3-pointer late in the game and was 11-for-12 from the free throw line, helping the Cyclones (16-4, 4-2) hand Kansas State (18-2, 5-2) just its second loss. The Wildcats also were beaten by then-No. 3 Oklahoma.

Shalee Lehning scored 15 points and Ashley Sweat added 14 for Kansas State.

Ezell scored 12 points in the Cyclones' 19-8 run down the stretch. Nicky Wieben was the only other ISU player in double figures with 13 points.
